KNOWN BUGS:

* It seems that advi does not find EPS files correctly.
I haven't tried to localized the bug, but my example was: 

    % kpsewhich Logo-INRIA-Rocq.eps       
    /home/morgon/remy/lib/tex/Logo-INRIA-Rocq.eps

while from the same path:

     % advi cely.dvi
     Warning: Logo-INRIA-Rocq.eps is not found. (Error while executing kpsewhich Logo-INRIA-Rocq.eps > /tmp/advi48)

Probably textdir-path is in cause: the way tex tools work is to use the
environment variable YYYINPUTS where YYY is the name of the command
(e.g. TEX, LATEX, DVI, etc) which some inheritance between them. 

In search.ml, the use of "/usr/share/texmf/ls-R" is erroneously plug as the
only place for tex data base. I use TEXINPUTS with several subdirectories, 
each of which ending with // which means not to look for ls-R bur
recursively to look through the whole directory, recursively.

Unless this semantics is implemented, we should expect bug reports 

  - from people who install texmf in another directory
  - from people who personalized their TEXINPUTS


LIMITATIONS:

* PStricks ne marche pas correctement avec \ncarc etc. (annotation sur les
  flèches). 


